                     <interp inst="t18340904-245-defend1444" type="age" value="28"></interp>
                  </persName>
             was indicted for <rs id="t18340904-245-off1370" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18340904-245-off1370" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18340904-245-off1370" type="offenceSubcategory" value="simpleLarceny"></interp>
               stealing, on the <rs id="t18340904-245-cd1371" type="crimeDate">21st of July</rs>
                     <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18340904-245-off1370 t18340904-245-cd1371"></join>, 19 handkerchiefs, value 4l. 15s.; 9 pair of stockings, value 3l.; 24 pair of cotton stockings, value 1l. 16s.; 16 shirts, value 5l.; 12 towels, value 4s.; 6 night shirts, value 12s.; 1 dressing coat, value 18s.; and 1 night cap, value 9s.
            </rs>; the goods of 
               <persName id="t18340904-245-victim1445" type="victimName">
                  Ann 
                  Porter
               <interp inst="t18340904-245-victim1445" type="surname" value="Porter"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18340904-245-victim1445" type="given" value="Ann"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18340904-245-victim1445" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                     <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18340904-245-off1370 t18340904-245-victim1445"></join>
                  </persName>
            .</p>
               <p>MR. ADOLPHUS conducted the Prosecution.</p>
               <p>ANN PORTER. I am a <rs id="t18340904-245-viclabel1372" type="occupation">widow</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18340904-245-victim1445 t18340904-245-viclabel1372"></join>, and <rs id="t18340904-245-viclabel1373" type="occupation">keep an outfitting warehouse</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18340904-245-victim1445 t18340904-245-viclabel1373"></join>, at <placeName id="t18340904-245-crimeloc1374">Charing-cross</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18340904-245-crimeloc1374" type="placeName" value="Charing-cross"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18340904-245-crimeloc1374" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18340904-245-off1370 t18340904-245-crimeloc1374"></join>. In July last, the prisoner came and said she had recommended my house to old Mr. and Mrs. Varley, her husband's father and mother - that they wanted a great many things; and first, they would have some silk handkerchiefs and stockings to choose from- I had my bonnet on, and was going out - I told my young woman to show the handkerchiefs - she said they were to be shown to Mr. and Mrs. Varley, and to be returned if not approved - she came several times, and at last I began to have some suspicion.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by MR. DOANE. Q. Has not she been in the habit of dealing at your house for some years? A. Yes; since October, 1831 - either she or her husband paid for the goods she had - she asked for the running credit of twelve months, which she had, and paid soon after Christmas, but it was of small amount - we entered the goods she had in the waste book, which is here - I entered these goods to Mrs. Varley, but supposing it was for old Mrs. Varley - this entry was similar to the previous entries - I made out a bill of parcels to Mrs. Varley - I did not write"Old Mrs. Varley's."</p>
               <p>MR. ADOLPHUS. Q. Would you have let her have these things for herself? A. No, not in any way; her entries before this were not more than 8l. in a year - I knew old Mr. and Mrs. Varley by report, and one of the parcels was directed to Pangbourn, near Reading.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18340904-245-person1446">
                  ELIZA 
                  GUY
               <interp inst="t18340904-245-person1446" type="surname" value="GUY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18340904-245-person1446" type="given" value="ELIZA"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18340904-245-person1446" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was in the prosecutrix's shop when the prisoner came for these things - I heard her say she had recommended Mrs. Porter to Mr. Varley, of Pangbourn, and she wished to have some handkerchiefs and other things - Mrs. Porter was going out, and I made up the order - I offered to send it, but she took it away herself - the goods were to be taken back or exchanged, if not approved by old Mr. and Mrs. Varley - the next day, she came again - she said two of the silk handkerchiefs were not approved of, and she looked out seven others - she wanted some more of the stockings, but we had none - she came again, and went on dealing, till the bill came to 25l.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined. Q. You entered the goods to Mrs. Varley? A. Yes, as we had before; and I gave her a memorandum of them, as she said they would want to know the price - I knew they were not for her.</p>
               <p>MR. 
               <persName id="t18340904-245-person1447">
                  JOHN 
                  BENJAMIN VARLEY
               <interp inst="t18340904-245-person1447" type="surname" value="BENJAMIN VARLEY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18340904-245-person1447" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18340904-245-person1447" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am the prisoner's hus<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183409040127"></xptr>band's father - I never commissioned her to buy goods for me or my wife - I never saw her till she was at Bow-street.</p>
               <p>MRS. 
               <persName id="t18340904-245-person1448">
                  MARTHA 
                  VARLEY
               <interp inst="t18340904-245-person1448" type="surname" value="VARLEY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18340904-245-person1448" type="given" value="MARTHA"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18340904-245-person1448" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I never commissioned the prisoner to buy any goods - I never received any.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18340904-245-person1449">
                  THOMAS 
                  BIRKETT
               <interp inst="t18340904-245-person1449" type="surname" value="BIRKETT"></interp>
